text: [Music]
hello I'm shab a technical customer
support engineer here at the AWS office
in Cape Town today I'll show you what to
do if you receive an error when you
respond to the capture to sign into your
AWS account let's get
started if you can't complete the
capture when you sign into an existing
AWS account or you activate a new one
then use these steps to troubleshoot the
issue clear your browser cache and
cookies use a different web
browser if you're on a mobile device try
using a desktop browser
instead wait 15 minutes then try to sign
in
again if you continue to have issues
after you follow these trouble shooting
steps you must contact Amazon customer
service for further
assistance to contact customer service
you have a few options for support in
the US and Canada call 1
for international phone support call
1364 note that some charges might apply
to these calls also note that customer
service can contact you only from the
number that's linked to your AWS account
because of the security policies that
are set by AWS when you speak with the
customer service representative be sure
to inform them that you can't pass the
amazon security verification prompt and
that the issue blocks you when you try
to log into your AWS account the
representative will investigate the
issue further and then provide
additional troubleshooting steps or
resolutions so now you know what to do
if you receive an error when you respond
to the capture to sign into your AWS
account thank you for watching and happy
cloud computing from all of us here at
AWS
